rait%20of%20OceanGate%20co-founders%20Guillermo%20S%C3%B6hnlein%20and%20Stockton%20Rush%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F666e5f21764df161125a390d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGuillermo%20S%C3%B6hnlein%2C%20left%2C%20co-founded%20OceanGate%20with%20the%20late%20Stockton%20Rush%2C%20right%2C%20in%202009.%3Cp%3EGuillermo%20S%C3%B6hnlein%2C%20Bill%20Sikes%2FAP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EOceanGate's%20Titan%20imploded%20nearly%20a%20year%20ago%2C%20killing%20all%205%20passengers%20including%20the%20company's%20CEO.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20company's%20co-founder%2C%20Guillermo%20S%C3%B6hnlein%2C%20told%20BI%20he%20thinks%20about%20the%20incident%20daily.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20fatal%20implosion%20motivates%20him%20to%20continue%20with%20his%20exploration%20ventures%2C%C2%A0S%C3%B6hnlein%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOceanGate's%20co-founder%20said%20he%20thinks%20about%20the%20fatal%20Titan%20submersible%20voyage%20every%20day%2C%20and%20the%20incident%20pushes%20him%20to%20continue%20pursuing%20his%20vision%20of%20accessible%20deep-sea%20exploration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENearly%20one%20year%20ago%2C%20on%20June%2018%2C%202023%2C%20the%20Titan%20made%20its%20final%20plunge%20in%20the%20Atlantic%2C%20where%20five%20passengers%20%E2%80%94%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwho-is-stockton-rush-lost-ceo-titan-submarine-oceangate-titanic-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOceanGate's%20CEO%20Stockton%20Rush%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20ventured%20to%20the%20site%20of%20the%20Titanic%20wreckage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20Coast%20Guard%20officials%20said%20the%20vessel%20experienced%20a%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpassengers-titan-submersible-dead-oceangate-titanic-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecatastrophic%20implosion%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20instantly%20killing%20all%20passengers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20incident%20captured%20national%20attention%20and%20was%20widely%20viewed%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foceangate-ceo-stockton-rush-wanted-elon-musk-doomed-titanic-sub-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emanifestation%20of%20Rush's%20hubris%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20relentless%20push%20to%20explore%20the%20deep%20sea%20%E2%80%94%20even%20if%20that%20meant%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foceangate-ceo-stockton-rush-broken-some-rules-titanic-sub-remembered-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebending%20a%20few%20rules%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFew%20of%20us%20ever%20have%20a%20fatal%20flaw%2C%20and%20Rush%20did%2C%26quot%3B%20Arnie%20Weissmann%2C%20the%20editor-in-chief%20of%20Travel%20Weekly%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20last%20year.%20%26quot%3BHe%20thought%20he%20was%20right%20or%20he%20wouldn't%20have%20gotten%20in%20%5Bthe%20submersible%5D%20and%20piloted%20it%2C%20but%20that%20was%20a%20fatal%20flaw.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20for%20Guillermo%20S%C3%B6hnlein%2C%20who%20co-founded%20OceanGate%20with%20Rush%20in%202009%2C%20death%20is%20an%20unfortunate%20element%20of%20innovation%20that%20explorers%20can%20only%20hope%20to%20avoid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20always%20know%20that%20setbacks%20are%20almost%20just%20part%20of%20the%20exploration%20experience.%20It's%20almost%20in%20the%20definition%20of%20exploration%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20BI%20in%20a%20recent%20interview.%20%26quot%3BYou're%20gonna%20have%20setbacks%2C%20and%20you%20hope%20that%20the%20setbacks%20don't%20include%20fatalities%2C%20but%20you%20know%20that's%20a%20possibility.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20when%20death%20does%20become%20a%20%26quot%3Bsetback%2C%26quot%3B%20S%C3%B6hnlein%20said%2C%20that's%20when%20you%20should%20push%20harder.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20in%20a%20paradoxical%20kind%20of%20way%2C%20that%20drive%20to%20keep%20going%20is%20amplified%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20I%20think%20in%20large%20part%2C%20it's%20because%20you%20want%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20your%20colleagues%2C%20who%20lost%20their%20lives%2C%20didn't%20lose%20their%20lives%20in%20vain.%20You%20want%20their%20death%20to%20mean%20something%2C%20and%20you%20want%20their%20legacies%20to%20live%20on.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20sentiment%20is%20part%20of%20why%20S%C3%B6hnlein%20hasn't%20stopped%20thinking%20about%20OceanGate%20and%20Rush%20in%20the%20year%20since%20the%20Titan%20catastrophe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20anything%20I%20probably%20think%20about%20him%20and%20the%20company%20and%20everything%2010%20times%20more%20than%20I%20did%20before%20the%20incident%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bd9c618a-e67d-4632-a9e4-ad7440442801%5C%22%3EAdvances%20in%20human%20transportation%20systems%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20interview%2C%20S%C3%B6hnlein%20did%20not%20mention%20regrets%20in%20those%20thoughts%20but%20rather%20a%20desire%20to%20achieve%20OceanGate's%20early%20vision%20to%20%26quot%3Bopen%20the%20oceans%20up%20to%20humanity.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20told%20BI%20that%20he%20sees%20an%20issue%20with%20how%20the%20only%20people%20who%20seem%20to%20be%20able%20to%20plunge%20into%20the%20ocean's%20depths%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flarry-connor-billionaire-titanic-wreck-submersible-oceangate-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebillionaires%20with%20resources%20to%20build%20a%20submersible%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20researchers%20and%20government%20agencies%20that%20have%20access%20to%20deep-sea%20vessels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20Stockton%20and%20I%20sat%20down%20and%20looked%20at%20the%20state%20of%20the%20world%20in%202009%2C%20we%20thought%2C%20'That%20is%20a%20tragedy%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20most%20important%20ecosystem%20in%20the%20entire%20planet%20is%20one%20that%20we%20can%20only%20a