Business%20Insider%20previously%20reported%2C%20and%20Gates%20is%20%26quot%3Bquite%20confident%26quot%3B%20the%20project%20will%20move%20forward%20regardless%20of%20who%20wins%20the%20White%20House%20or%20the%20Congressional%20majority%20in%20November.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTheir%20support%20for%20nuclear%20power%20is%20very%20impressive%20in%20both%20parties%2C%26quot%3B%20Gates%20told%20CBS%20News%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbsnews.com%2Fvideo%2Fbill-gates-on-face-the-nation-with-margaret-brennan-full-interview%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BFace%20the%20Nation%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Sunday.%20%26quot%3BOf%20all%20the%20climate-related%20work%20I'm%20doing%2C%20I'd%20say%20the%20one%20that%20has%20the%20most%20bipartisan%20energy%20behind%20it%20is%20actually%20this%20nuclear%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20noted%20the%20reasons%20each%20party%20supports%20nuclear%20%26quot%3Bmay%20not%20be%20identical.%26quot%3B%20Republicans%20value%20energy%20security%20and%20exports%2C%20he%20said%2C%20while%20Democrats%20value%20both%20those%20issues%20and%20clean%20energy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNuclear%20really%20is%20a%20special%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20CBS.%20%26quot%3BNot%20because%20it's%20green%2C%20there%20are%20people%20who%20don't%20value%20that%20part%20of%20it%20all%2C%20I%20wish%20they%20would.%20They%20value%20it%20because%20of%20the%20US%20leadership.%20And%20you%20really%20don't%20want%20the%20nuclear%20reactors%20around%20the%20world%2C%20made%20by%20our%20adversaries%2C%20because%20it's%20economically%20a%20huge%20job%20creator.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENuclear%20energy%20is%20considered%20the%20largest%20source%20of%20clean%20power%20in%20the%20United%20States%20and%20is%20responsible%20for%20nearly%20half%20of%20the%20nation's%20emissions-free%20electricity%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.energy.gov%2Fne%2Farticles%2Fadvantages-and-challenges-nuclear-energy%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20the%20Office%20of%20Nuclear%20Energy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20US%20government%20agency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20produced%20in%20nuclear%20reactors%20through%20atomic%20fission%2C%20in%20which%20subatomic%20particles%20called%20neutrons%20collide%20with%20full%20atoms%2C%20forcing%20them%20to%20split%20in%20two.%20This%20process%20releases%20tons%20of%20heat%2C%20which%20is%20used%20to%20boil%20water%20and%20produce%20steam.%20That%20steam%20is%20then%20routed%20through%20the%20nuclear%20reactor's%20steam%20system%20to%20spin%20turbines%20and%20produce%20electricity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELawmakers%20on%20both%20sides%20of%20the%20aisle%20have%20worked%20to%20bolster%20the%20nuclear%20energy%20industry%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20March%2C%20the%20House%20of%20Representatives%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbucshon.house.gov%2Fnews%2Fdocumentsingle.aspx%3FDocumentID%3D4564%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epassed%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20ADVANCE%20Act%2C%20which%20will%20expand%20the%20use%20of%20nuclear%20energy%20in%20the%20United%20States%20and%20abroad.%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20also%20signed%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.congress.gov%2Fbill%2F118th-congress%2Fhouse-bill%2F4366%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elaw%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20March%20that%20allocates%20%24100%20million%20to%20nuclear%20workforce%20training%20programs%20at%20universities%2C%20two-year%20colleges%2C%20and%20trade%20schools.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20renewed%20focus%20on%20nuclear%20energy%20also%20comes%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftop-artificial-intelligence-customer-experience-business-applications-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20development%20of%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%20surges.%20Tech%20companies%20like%20OpenAI%20are%20increasingly%20looking%20for%20cleaner%2C%20greener%20forms%20of%20energy%20to%20meet%20the%20huge%20power%20demands%20of%20their%20data%20centers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%